  "title": "Introduction to variables",
  "segments": [
    {
      "segment_id": 1,
      "text": "Welcome to algebra. Today we'll explore the fundamental concepts of variables and how they work.",
      "start_time": 0,
      "end_time": 8,
      "duration": 8,
      "allows_questions": true,
      "pause_duration": 2000,
      "topic_marker": "introduction"
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 2,
      "text": "A variable is a symbol, usually a letter, that represents a number we don't know yet.",
      "start_time": 8,
      "end_time": 15,
      "duration": 7,
      "allows_questions": true,
      "pause_duration": 1500,
      "topic_marker": "definition"
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 3,
      "text": "For example, if I say x equals 5, then x is our variable and 5 is its value.",
      "start_time": 15,
      "end_time": 22,
      "duration": 7,
      "allows_questions": true,
      "pause_duration": 2000,
      "topic_marker": "example"
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 4,
      "text": "Variables are powerful because they let us write general rules that work for any number.",
      "start_time": 22,
      "end_time": 30,
      "duration": 8,
      "allows_questions": true,
      "pause_duration": 2000,
      "topic_marker": "concept"
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 5,
      "text": "Let's look at a simple equation: x plus 3 equals 7. What value of x makes this true?",
      "start_time": 30,
      "end_time": 38,
      "duration": 8,
      "allows_questions": true,
      "pause_duration": 3000,
      "topic_marker": "practice"
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 6,
      "text": "If we subtract 3 from both sides, we get x equals 4. So x is 4.",
      "start_time": 38,
      "end_time": 45,
      "duration": 7,
      "allows_questions": true,
      "pause_duration": 2000,
      "topic_marker": "solution"
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 7,
      "text": "This is the foundation of algebra - using operations to find unknown values.",
      "start_time": 45,
      "end_time": 52,
      "duration": 7,
      "allows_questions": true,
      "pause_duration": 2000,
      "topic_marker": "summary"
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 8,
      "text": "In the next lesson, we'll explore more complex equations and multiple variables.",
      "start_time": 52,
      "end_time": 60,
      "duration": 8,
      "allows_questions": true,
      "pause_duration": 1000,
      "topic_marker": "transition"
    }
  ],
